  "description": "End-to-end operational overview of the self-hosted Nextcloud service.\n\nThe top row focuses on service health as seen from the outside: HTTP reachability of /status.php, 24-hour success rate, and availability of the backing MariaDB and Redis instances (via dedicated exporters).\n\nThe second row provides load and capacity signals for the database and cache layers (queries per second, active connections, Redis commands and clients), helping correlate latency spikes with changes in backend activity.\n\nThe bottom row surfaces application logs from the nc-app container, separating unexpected errors from known noisy diagnostics. This allows quick triage of real issues while keeping recurring but non-critical patterns visible for awareness.\n\nIntended use: day-to-day monitoring of Nextcloud, quick incident triage, and portfolio-style demonstration of observability practices around a single, production-like application stack.",
